body:
I means a parenthesized method declarations.
The same as declared the class members (inside a `class name { }`).
This does not complicates the grammar because currently `method declaration` looks like:

```
MethodDecl   = "func" Receiver MethodName ( Function | Signature ) .
Receiver     = Parameters .
```

What means the following:

```
MethodDecls      = "func" Receiver "("  PartMethodDecl* ")"

PartMethodDecl   = MethodName ( Function | Signature ) .
Receiver     = Parameters .
```
